data.description: Step back in time and embrace the enchantment of the 1900s with this captivating HWY 115 home, nestled just off Main St. This residence, boasting 4 bedrooms and 3 bathrooms, seamlessly blends classic charm with modern convenience. As you enter, you'll be greeted by the heart of the home – a generous kitchen adorned with stainless steel appliances, abundant counter space, a center island, breakfast bar, and a roomy pantry, catering to the needs of culinary enthusiasts. Sunlight dances through a wall of brand new windows, casting a warm and inviting glow throughout the interior. The large family room invites relaxation, featuring a cozy pellet stove, perfect for chilly evenings spent in the embrace of classic comfort. A private retreat awaits. A half bath and a master bedroom with a handicap-accessible step-in tub and a walk-in closet offer a haven of tranquility. Practicality meets elegance with an office space complete with a built-in gun safe. Updates throughout the home include new flooring, barnwood doors, fresh paint, new windows with a warranty and modern light fixtures, seamlessly merging classic charm with contemporary comfort. The utility area ensures ample storage, maintaining the living spaces clutter-free. Venture outdoors to discover an impressive heated 50x30 shop with a newer roof, a fenced backyard, covered carport, RV parking with alley access, and a delightful garden. Hollyhock flowers adorn the front, adding to the home's timeless charm.
